{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"As technology progresses,"},{"time":3000,"text":"and as it advances,"},{"time":5000,"text":"many of us assume that these advances"},{"time":7000,"text":"make us more intelligent,"},{"time":9000,"text":"make us smarter and more connected to the world."},{"time":11000,"text":"And what I'd like to argue"},{"time":13000,"text":"is that that's not necessarily the case,"},{"time":15000,"text":"as progress is simply a word for change,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and with change you gain something,"},{"time":20000,"text":"but you also lose something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22000,"text":"And to really illustrate this point, what I'd like to do"},{"time":24000,"text":"is to show you how technology has dealt with"},{"time":27000,"text":"a very simple, a very common, an everyday question."},{"time":32000,"text":"And that question is this."},{"time":34000,"text":"What time is it? What time is it?"},{"time":37000,"text":"If you glance at your iPhone, it's so simple to tell the time."},{"time":40000,"text":"But, I'd like to ask you, how would you tell the time"},{"time":42000,"text":"if you didn't have an iPhone?"},{"time":44000,"text":"How would you tell the time, say, 600 years ago?"},{"time":47000,"text":"How would you do it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":49000,"text":"Well, the way you would do it is by using a device"},{"time":52000,"text":"that's called an astrolabe."},{"time":56000,"text":"So, an astrolabe is relatively unknown in today's world."},{"time":60000,"text":"But, at the time, in the 13th century,"},{"time":62000,"text":"it was the gadget of the day."},{"time":64000,"text":"It was the world's first popular computer."},{"time":68000,"text":"And it was a device that, in fact, is a model of the sky."},{"time":72000,"text":"So, the different parts of the astrolabe, in this particular type,"},{"time":74000,"text":"the rete corresponds to the positions of the stars."},{"time":77000,"text":"The plate corresponds to a coordinate system."},{"time":80000,"text":"And the mater has some scales and puts it all together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"If you were an educated child,"},{"time":86000,"text":"you would know how to not only use the astrolabe,"},{"time":88000,"text":"you would also know how to make an astrolabe."},{"time":91000,"text":"And we know this because the first treatise on the astrolabe,"},{"time":94000,"text":"the first technical manual in the English language,"},{"time":96000,"text":"was written by Geoffrey Chaucer."},{"time":98000,"text":"Yes, that Geoffrey Chaucer, in 1391,"},{"time":101000,"text":"to his little Lewis, his 11-year-old son."},{"time":105000,"text":"And in this book, little Lewis would know the big idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110000,"text":"And the central idea that makes this computer work"},{"time":112000,"text":"is this thing called stereographic projection."},{"time":115000,"text":"And basically, the concept is,"},{"time":117000,"text":"how do you represent the three-dimensional image"},{"time":120000,"text":"of the night sky that surrounds us"},{"time":122000,"text":"onto a flat, portable, two-dimensional surface."},{"time":125000,"text":"The idea is actually relatively simple."},{"time":127000,"text":"Imagine that that Earth is at the center of the universe,"},{"time":130000,"text":"and surrounding it is the sky projected onto a sphere."},{"time":133000,"text":"Each point on the surface of the sphere"},{"time":136000,"text":"is mapped through the bottom pole,"},{"time":138000,"text":"onto a flat surface, where it is then recorded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140000,"text":"So the North Star corresponds to the center of the device."},{"time":144000,"text":"The ecliptic, which is the path of the sun, moon, and planets"},{"time":147000,"text":"correspond to an offset circle."},{"time":149000,"text":"The bright stars correspond to little daggers on the rete."},{"time":153000,"text":"And the altitude corresponds to the plate system."},{"time":156000,"text":"Now, the real genius of the astrolabe is not just the projection."},{"time":159000,"text":"The real genius is that it brings together two coordinate systems"},{"time":163000,"text":"so they fit perfectly."},{"time":165000,"text":"There is the position of the sun, moon and planets on the movable rete."},{"time":168000,"text":"And then there is their location on the sky"},{"time":170000,"text":"as seen from a certain latitude on the back plate. Okay?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":175000,"text":"So how would you use this device?"},{"time":180000,"text":"Well, let me first back up for a moment."},{"time":186000,"text":"This is an astrolabe. Pretty impressive, isn't it?"},{"time":191000,"text":"And so, this astrolabe is on loan from us"},{"time":194000,"text":"from the Oxford School of -- Museum of History."},{"time":197000,"text":"And you can see the different components."},{"time":200000,"text":"This is the mater, the scales on the back."},{"time":202000,"text":"This is the rete. Okay. Do you see that?"},{"time":204000,"text":"That's the movable part of the sky."},{"time":207000,"text":"And in the back you can see"},{"time":209000,"text":"a spider web pattern."},{"time":211000,"text":"And that spider web pattern corresponds to the local coordinates in the sky."},{"time":215000,"text":"This is a rule device. And on the back"},{"time":217000,"text":"are some other devices, measuring tools"},{"time":220000,"text":"and scales, to be able to make some calculations. Okay?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":226000,"text":"You know, I've always wanted one of these."},{"time":228000,"text":"For my thesis I actually built one of these out of paper."},{"time":233000,"text":"And this one, this is a replica"},{"time":235000,"text":"from a 15th-century device."},{"time":238000,"text":"And it's worth probably about three MacBook Pros."},{"time":241000,"text":"But a real one would cost about as much as my house,"},{"time":244000,"text":"and the house next to it, and actually every house on the block,"},{"time":247000,"text":"on both sides of the street,"},{"time":249000,"text":"maybe a school thrown in, and some -- you know, a church."},{"time":251000,"text":"They are just incredibly expensive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253000,"text":"But let me show you how to work this device."},{"time":255000,"text":"So let's go to step one."},{"time":258000,"text":"First thing that you do is you select a star"},{"time":260000,"text":"in the night sky, if you're telling time at night."},{"time":263000,"text":"So, tonight, if it's clear you'll be able to see the summer triangle."},{"time":266000,"text":"And there is a bright star called Deneb. So let's select Deneb."},{"time":269000,"text":"Second, is you measure the altitude of Deneb."},{"time":272000,"text":"So, step two, I hold the device up,"},{"time":275000,"text":"and then I sight its altitude there"},{"time":278000,"text":"so I can see it clearly now."},{"time":280000,"text":"And then I measure its altitude."},{"time":283000,"text":"So, it's about 26 degrees. You can't see it from over there."},{"time":286000,"text":"Step three is identify the star on the front of the device."},{"time":291000,"text":"Deneb is there. I can tell."},{"time":293000,"text":"Step four is I then move the rete,"},{"time":296000,"text":"move the sky, so the altitude of the star"},{"time":299000,"text":"corresponds to the scale on the back."},{"time":302000,"text":"Okay, so when that happens"},{"time":305000,"text":"everything lines up."},{"time":307000,"text":"I have here a model of the sky"},{"time":309000,"text":"that corresponds to the real sky. Okay?"},{"time":312000,"text":"So, it is, in a sense,"},{"time":314000,"text":"holding a model of the universe in my hands."},{"time":317000,"text":"And then finally, I take a rule,"},{"time":320000,"text":"and move the rule to a date line"},{"time":322000,"text":"which then tells me the time here."},{"time":325000,"text":"Right. So, that's how the device is used."},{"time":328000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":329000,"text":"So, I know what you're thinking:"},{"time":331000,"text":"\"That's a lot of work, isn't it? Isn't it a ton of work to be able to tell the time?\""},{"time":335000,"text":"as you glance at your iPod to just check out the time."},{"time":339000,"text":"But there is a difference between the two, because with your iPod"},{"time":341000,"text":"you can tell -- or your iPhone, you can tell exactly"},{"time":344000,"text":"what the time is, with precision."},{"time":346000,"text":"The way little Lewis would tell the time"},{"time":348000,"text":"is by a picture of the sky."},{"time":350000,"text":"He would know where things would fit in the sky."},{"time":353000,"text":"He would not only know what time it was,"},{"time":356000,"text":"he would also know where the sun would rise,"},{"time":358000,"text":"and how it would move across the sky."},{"time":361000,"text":"He would know what time the sun would rise, and what time it would set."},{"time":365000,"text":"And he would know that for essentially every celestial object"},{"time":367000,"text":"in the heavens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369000,"text":"So, in computer graphics"},{"time":371000,"text":"and computer user interface design,"},{"time":374000,"text":"there is a term called affordances."},{"time":377000,"text":"So, affordances are the qualities of an object"},{"time":380000,"text":"that allow us to perform an action with it."},{"time":383000,"text":"And what the astrolabe does is it allows us,"},{"time":385000,"text":"it affords us, to connect to the night sky,"},{"time":388000,"text":"to look up into the night sky and be much more --"},{"time":391000,"text":"to see the visible and the invisible together."},{"time":394000,"text":"So, that's just one use. Incredible,"},{"time":398000,"text":"there is probably 350, 400 uses."},{"time":401000,"text":"In fact, there is a text, and that has over a thousand uses"},{"time":403000,"text":"of this first computer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405000,"text":"On the back there is scales and measurements"},{"time":407000,"text":"for terrestrial navigation."},{"time":409000,"text":"You can survey with it. The city of Baghdad was surveyed with it."},{"time":412000,"text":"It can be used for calculating mathematical equations of all different types."},{"time":416000,"text":"And it would take a full university course to illustrate it."},{"time":419000,"text":"Astrolabes have an incredible history."},{"time":421000,"text":"They are over 2,000 years old."},{"time":423000,"text":"The concept of stereographic projection"},{"time":426000,"text":"originated in 330 B.C."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428000,"text":"And the astrolabes come in many different"},{"time":430000,"text":"sizes and shapes and forms."},{"time":432000,"text":"There is portable ones. There is large display ones."},{"time":435000,"text":"And I think what is common to all astrolabes"},{"time":437000,"text":"is that they are beautiful works of art."},{"time":439000,"text":"There is a quality of craftsmanship and precision"},{"time":442000,"text":"that is just astonishing and remarkable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445000,"text":"Astrolabes, like every technology, do evolve over time."},{"time":448000,"text":"So, the earliest retes, for example, were very simple and primitive."},{"time":452000,"text":"And advancing retes became cultural emblems."},{"time":454000,"text":"This is one from Oxford."},{"time":457000,"text":"And I find this one really extraordinary because the rete pattern"},{"time":459000,"text":"is completely symmetrical,"},{"time":461000,"text":"and it accurately maps a completely asymmetrical, or random sky."},{"time":465000,"text":"How cool is that? This is just amazing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467000,"text":"So, would little Lewis have an astrolabe?"},{"time":470000,"text":"Probably not one made of brass. He would have one made out of wood,"},{"time":473000,"text":"or paper. And the vast majority of this first computer"},{"time":476000,"text":"was a portable device"},{"time":478000,"text":"that you could keep in the back of your pocket."},{"time":481000,"text":"So, what does the astrolabe inspire?"},{"time":484000,"text":"Well, I think the first thing is that"},{"time":486000,"text":"it reminds us just how resourceful people were,"},{"time":490000,"text":"our forebears were, years and years ago."},{"time":492000,"text":"It's just an incredible device."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495000,"text":"Every technology advances."},{"time":497000,"text":"Every technology is transformed and moved by others."},{"time":500000,"text":"And what we gain with a new technology, of course,"},{"time":502000,"text":"is precision and accuracy."},{"time":504000,"text":"But what we lose, I think, is"},{"time":506000,"text":"an accurate -- a felt sense"},{"time":509000,"text":"of the sky, a sense of context."},{"time":512000,"text":"Knowing the sky, knowing your relationship with the sky,"},{"time":516000,"text":"is the center of the real answer"},{"time":520000,"text":"to knowing what time it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522000,"text":"So, it's -- I think astrolabes are just remarkable devices."},{"time":526000,"text":"And so, what can you learn from these devices?"},{"time":529000,"text":"Well, primarily that there is a subtle knowledge"},{"time":532000,"text":"that we can connect with the world."},{"time":534000,"text":"And astrolabes return us to this subtle sense"},{"time":537000,"text":"of how things all fit together,"},{"time":540000,"text":"and also how we connect to the world."},{"time":542000,"text":"Thanks very much."},{"time":544000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}